RN  [1]
RM  9714766
RT  Cloning of conserved genes from Zymomonas mobilis and Bradyrhizobium
RT  japonicum that function in the biosynthesis of hopanoid lipids.
RA  Perzl M, Reipen IG, Schmitz S, Poralla K, Sahm H, Sprenger GA,
RA  Kannenberg EL;
RL  Biochim Biophys Acta. 1998;1393:108-118.
CC  Hopanoids are pentacyclic steroid-like compounds derived from squalene
CC  (a diterpene) by cyclization and various elaborations of the side
CC  chain. Methylations of the polycyclic body of the molecule have also
CC  been reported. The essential enzymes are squalene synthase which
CC  condenses two molecules of farnesyl-pyrophosphate and squalene-hopene
CC  cyclase.
